<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/834f5b6f68c592821644ca726df8a34d.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 9 and b = 4. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>9.8</li><li>66.0</li><li>24.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}^{{2}}+{4}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={81}+{16}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={97}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{97}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.8488578017961}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.8}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{9}}{{4}}\right)}}}\approx{66.037511025422}\approx{66}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{66.037511025422}^{\circ}\approx{23.962488974578}\approx{24}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

